Netizen contribution
On July 18, the Central Cyberspace Affairs Commission launched a special rectification of the Internet environment of the "Chengdu Universiade".
The rectification content includes:
Hype negative topics involving college students;
Incite ethnic and regional groups to confront each other;
In the name of recording life and helping and rescuing, fabricate and stage local poverty life to attract traffic;
Spread false information in the fields of public policy and social livelihood in relevant regions, fabricate disasters, crimes, and food product quality problems that may cause panic;
Disclose privacy, insult, slander, and abuse athletes, referees, and coaches.
Illegal broadcasting, infringement of emblems and mascots, etc.
